d by leadership.\n\nJob Duties:\n\u2022 Define complex and detailed statistical analyses and modeling of clinical and operational data with outputs that are clear and relevant to stakeholders; such as opportunity analyses, clinical trending, operational KPIs, predictive modeling, program evaluation, customer reporting, product development, and ad-hoc analytics.\n\u2022 Participate in the design and development of statistical analyses and reports that explore and present large amounts of data to discover underlying patterns and trends related to volumes, operational efficiency, cohort analysis, and clinical performance.\n\u2022 Apply research and evaluation standards, descriptive statistics, and data management principles to translate complex data into meaningful content.\n\u2022 Through the use of risk stratification approximate the spend of different patient populations to mitigate unnecessary spend. Develop models and understanding of value-based care and shared savings contracts to provide scenarios to full valuation to maximize potential revenue.\n\u2022 Working with the Clinical Director of Population Health design models of care to focus on specific patient populations to define clinical protocols and care pathways. Analyze patient data to stratify patients by risk profile to ensure each patient receives the right care at the right time.\n\u2022 Present findings using verbal, written, and graphic communication techniques. Offer recommendations to support organizational performance improvement.\n\u2022 Independently complete analysis, development, and enhancement of analytical and operational BI solutions to fulfill business needs.\n\u2022 Apply understanding of dimensional data modeling techniques, data warehousing, design, and concepts to produce balanced scorecard design, and design of dashboards and KPI\u2019s (Key Performance Indicators).\n\u2022 Stay informed about Business Intelligence industry trends, technologies and best practices that can be applied to achieve organizational objectives.\n\u2022 Analyze large data sets of structured, semi-structured unstructured data to discover data insights and collaborate with business partners to deliver business value to discover trends, patterns, and actionable insights.\n\u2022 Design interactive and/or advanced visualizations (Tableau) that enhance analytics storytelling to support business decisions.\n\u2022 Navigate multiple business lines and draw holistic insights from large data sets.\n\u2022 Interpret and develop complex SQL queries for both ad-hoc and ETL uses.\n\u2022 Provides direction and guidance to less experienced team members.\n\u2022 Performs all other duties as assigned.\n\nEducation:\n\nBachelor\u2019s Degree in Business Analytics, Data Science, Health Analytics Computer Science, Management Information Systems, Information Technology or any other scientific, technical, healthcare informatics, or mathematics field. Four (4) years of comparable experience may be substituted for a degree.\n\nExperience:\n\nOne (1) to Five (5) years of directly related Epic experience including in-depth knowledge of data analytics, data science, data warehousing, data lakes and marts, and metadata management, and dimensional is preferred. Healthcare background with experience in Population Health and Value-based Care models preferred.\n\nAdditional Knowledge, License, and Certifications:\n\nCertified in Tableau is preferred. Proficiency with sophisticated analytics tools and programming languages (SAS, R, Python, Java, Spark, Hadoop, Alteryx, SQL); proficiency with data visualization tools (Tableau, QlikView, and others). As specified by the department director, additional certifications for assigned software analytical tools (such as Tableau). Certification must be maintained per Health-IT standards.\n\nCertified in Epic Cogito Data Warehouse & Caboodle Data Model. Epic certification must be maintained per Epic Corporation standards within 180 days of hire is required.\n\nA